.TH "guest_translate_address" 9 "guest_translate_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
guest_translate_address \- translate guest logical into guest absolute address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" guest_translate_address
.BI "(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ","
.BI "unsigned long gva "  ","
.BI "u8 ar "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *gpa "  ","
.BI "enum gacc_mode mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vcpu" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "gva" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "ar" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "gpa" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "mode" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Parameter semantics are the same as the ones from guest_translate.
The memory contents at the guest address are not changed.
.SH "NOTE"
The IPTE lock is not taken during this function, so the caller
has to take care of this.
